- "Bountiful" refers to the portfolios that have a high number of stocks;
- "Listed from the most abundant to the least" means the results are ordered by the number of stocks in descending order.

- 'reaped the greatest harvest' refers to the portfolios with the highest profit/loss value;
- 'current value' is the total current value of the stocks in the portfolio;
- 'net gain or loss' is the total profit or loss value of the stocks in the portfolio;
- 'percentage change in value' is the total profit or loss percentage of the stocks in the portfolio.

